  "A farmer applies large amounts of nitrogen fertilizer to crop fields that border a river flowing into a lake. Over the summer, the lake turns green and fish begin dying. Which concept best explains this chain of events?": "",
  "Thermal pollution from industrial discharge": "",
  "Acid deposition lowering the pH of the lake water": "",
  "Bioaccumulation of heavy metals in fish tissue": "",
  "Cultural eutrophication caused by nutrient runoff leading to algal blooms and oxygen depletion": "",
  "Excess nitrogen from fertilizer runs off into the waterway, triggering algal blooms that block sunlight and, upon decomposition, deplete dissolved oxygen, creating conditions lethal to fish and other aquatic organisms.": "",
  "A coastal fishing village notices that fish populations have collapsed after decades of increasing catch sizes. Despite no pollution or habitat destruction, the fish stocks continue declining even after catch limits are imposed. Which concept best explains this situation?": "",
  "Eutrophication from agricultural runoff": "",
  "Primary succession following a volcanic eruption": "",
  "Demographic transition in the village population": "",
  "The tragedy of the commons, where overharvesting of a shared resource exceeded the population's capacity to recover": "",
  "This scenario illustrates the tragedy of the commons: individual fishers maximized their personal catch from a shared resource until the fish population fell below its reproductive replacement level, making recovery difficult even with regulations.": "",
  "Scientists studying a forest ecosystem discover that removing wolves caused deer to overgraze vegetation, leading to riverbank erosion, loss of bird species, and decline of aquatic insects. What concept does this illustrate?": "",
